Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Muscat, 12 Feb (WAKH)--Sa'id Bin-Ahmad al-Shanfari, 
Omani petroleum and minerals minister, has announced that all 
non-OPEC oil producing countries have agreed to cut down their 
oil production, and that they are ready for this decision at any 
time. 
  The Omani News Agency said at noon today that al-Shanfari's 
statement came following a phone call he made to 'Abdallah 
Bin-Hamad al-'Atiyah, Qatari energy and industry minister and 
the current OPEC president. 
  The Omani minister paid successful visits to a number of 
non-OPEC oil producing countries in December and January [words 
indistinct] stability of oil markets and boost prices [words 
indistinct] through reducing their oil output. 

